  "texts": [
    "Selected ToolsThe evaluation focuses on model-agnostic tools, meaning they should not depend on internal model components like weights or structural information, ensuring applicability to any black box model.",
    "This choice is dictated by the fact that these explainers are more generally applicable and make it easier to compare several classification models.",
    "Again, for comparability, we discard papers that require handcrafted inputs, such as checklists [28] or input explanations to be validated [30].",
    "Moreover, we consider only tools that have public, updated, and working Python code.",
    "Finally, we added transparent machine learning models to the above list that can be used as surrogates, i.e."
  ]
}